What’s new in SimpleImage 1.6• Snapshot previewsSnapshots now feature previews so you can see the images and movies in it before opening them.• Mac OS 8.5 savvinessSimpleImage takes advantage of the new goodies in Mac OS 8.5, like proportional scroll boxes, title bar icons and the new open/save dialog boxes.• Better backward compatibility, tooSimpleImage now supports System 7 better, with contextual menu support (!) and support for the path popup menu in windows’ title bars.• Bug fixesSeveral bug fixes make SimpleImage 1.6 more reliable on a wider range of Macs.• Numerous other small improvementsSmarter handling of movies in slide shows, a neato sliding transition effect between slide show items, the ability to open any Snapshot as a slide show, and more...